# Django M2 Architecture

## Clean Architecture

- Separation of concerns: helpers, API endpoints, serializers in distinct folders
- Multiple files, multiple subfolders, clean tree structure
- No mixing of concerns across layers

## Folder Structure (per Django app)

```
app_name/
├── api/                    # API endpoints (views)
│   └── v1/
│       └── endpoint_name/
│           └── views.py
├── serializers/            # All serializers
│   └── endpoint_name/
│       ├── request.py      # Request serializer for this endpoint
│       └── response.py     # Response serializer for this endpoint
├── helpers/                # App-specific helpers
│   └── ...
└── ...
```

## Serializers

- **One request serializer + one response serializer per endpoint**
- Never merge request/response into a single serializer
- Organize in `serializers/<endpoint_name>/request.py` and `response.py`
- Use predefined structures for every request and response

## Views

- **Class-based views only** — no function views
- Use mixins and advanced patterns where appropriate
- Keep simple; avoid overcomplication
- **Central registry**: `app/views.py` re-exports all views from `api/v1/<endpoint>/views.py`; URLs import from `app.views`

## Shared Package

- Enums, common types, shared utilities → dedicated package (e.g. `core` or `shared`)
- All Django apps import from this package
- Single source of truth for cross-app concerns
